Troubleshooting Wireless Network Connectivity Issues

Overview:
Users are experiencing problems connecting to the wireless network. This guide addresses common wireless connectivity issues.

Symptoms:

    Devices unable to connect to the Wi-Fi network.
    Intermittent or slow wireless connections.

Troubleshooting Steps:

    Check Wi-Fi router or access point status and settings.
    Verify wireless security settings, including the correct passphrase.
    Analyze signal strength and interference using tools like NetSpot or inSSIDer.
    Update wireless network drivers on client devices.
    Consider adjusting channel settings on the Wi-Fi router to minimize interference.

Additional Tips:

    Encourage users to forget and rejoin the Wi-Fi network on their devices.
    Implement MAC address filtering for additional security.
